Absolutely! Sorting a list of integers is a fun challenge that I'm ready to tackle with enthusiasm and energy! One way to sort the list without using built-in functions is to implement a simple sorting algorithm like Bubble Sort. Here's how you can do it in Java:

```java
public class SortIntegers {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] nums = {5, 2, 9, 1, 3, 8};

        bubbleSort(nums);

        System.out.println("Sorted Array:");
        for(int num : nums) {
            System.out.print(num + " ");
        }
    }

    public static void bubbleSort(int[] arr) {
        int n = arr.length;
        boolean swapped;

        for(int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++) {
            swapped = false;

            for(int j = 0; j < n - i - 1; j++) {
                if(arr[j] > arr[j+1]) {
                    int temp = arr[j];
                    arr[j] = arr[j+1];
                    arr[j+1] = temp;
                    swapped = true;
                }
            }

            if(!swapped) {
                break;
            }
        }
    }
}
```

